    "returncode": 0,
    "stdout": "{\n  \"issues\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"frankentorch-8u7\",\n      \"title\": \"Make with_no_grad and with_enable_grad actually panic-safe\",\n      \"description\": \" and  are documented as panic-safe RAII equivalents, but they currently leave grad-enabled stack state dirty if the closure unwinds before the matching exit call. Restore state on panic and add regression coverage in ft-api.\",\n      \"status\": \"in_progress\",\n      \"priority\": 1,\n      \"issue_type\": \"bug\",\n      \"created_at\": \"2026-04-07T01:36:28.552416242Z\",\n      \"created_by\": \"ubuntu\",\n      \"updated_at\": \"2026-04-07T01:36:32.246245736Z\",\n      \"source_repo\": \".\",\n      \"compaction_level\": 0,\n      \"original_size\": 0,\n      \"dependency_count\": 0,\n      \"dependent_count\": 0\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"frankentorch-xsp\",\n      \"title\": \"Investigate beads/frankensqlite page-reuse integrity warning after writes\",\n      \"description\": \"## Context\\n`frankentorch-c84` diagnosed the residual `br doctor` / `PRAGMA integrity_check` warning in the FrankenTorch tracker.\\n\\n## Findings\\n- live `.beads/beads.db` remained operational and in sync with `.beads/issues.jsonl`\\n- an isolated rebuild from canonical JSONL (`.beads/beads.db.rebuild_c84_20260407T013146Z`) reproduced the `Page N: never used` integrity warning\\n- a `VACUUM INTO` rewrite (`.beads/beads.db.vacuum_c84_20260407T013244Z`) passed `integrity_check`, `quick_check`, and `br doctor --db ...`\\n- after promoting the vacuumed copy to canonical `.beads/beads.db`, subsequent normal `br` operations reintroduced the warning (`page 19 is never used`)\\n\\n## Interpretation\\nThis looks like a `beads_rust` / frankensqlite writer bug or page-accounting bug, not JSONL drift and not unrecoverable logical data corruption.\\n\\n## Artifacts\\n- `artifacts/beads_recovery/c84_snapshot_20260407T013033Z/`\\n- `.beads/beads.db.rebuild_c84_20260407T013146Z`\\n- `.beads/beads.db.vacuum_c84_20260407T013244Z`\\n- `.beads/beads.db.bad_20260407T013409Z`\\n- `artifacts/beads_recovery/c84_checkpoint_test_20260407T013229Z.db`\\n\\n## Next step\\nTrace which write path (export, write_probe, cache rebuild, or WAL handling) is reintroducing unreachable pages after a clean vacuum.\",\n      \"status\": \"in_progress\",\n      \"priority\": 1,\n      \"issue_type\": \"bug\",\n      \"created_at\": \"2026-04-07T01:35:07.977449573Z\",\n      \"created_by\": \"ubuntu\",\n      \"updated_at\": \"2026-04-07T02:56:56.205047340Z\",\n      \"source_repo\": \".\",\n      \"compaction_level\": 0,\n      \"original_size\": 0,\n      \"dependency_count\": 0,\n      \"dependent_count\": 0\n    }\n  ],\n  \"total\": 2,\n  \"limit\": 50,\n  \"offset\": 0,\n  \"has_more\": false\n}\n",
